column5: fang and i went to lake joseph with a three other buddies what a day, fang and i arrived around 7.15 am you couldnt see 50 yards ahead of you for fog. so we loaded the arctic cat with tracks and hooked up to sleighs and off we went in the fog we droppped one guy  from tronto with his bike he didnt know were he was going. turned on gps and then headed to where we were going to fish . drilled holes and fang with first line down 1st fiish right away. over the day we did very well  between 5 guys .  biggest 26 in 4.8 oz great day little slushy comeing back but good weather and good fishing
Sounded like a great trip Malcolm... hope Paul has some pictures !
how much snow was on the lake??? thinking of heading up in a day or two
no snow on ice  at all was a little slippery in morning with just boots on almost went for a couple of tumbles trying to upload from photobucket not sure how
thanks i guess  the sled is staying home and taking the 4 wheeler
there were guys with sleds out there as well
